This paper deals with the design and implementation of network codes, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also emphasizes the distributed nature of the coding schemes, which falls under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces technical tools and algorithms that may be of independent interest, which could place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
